<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-18T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-18T13:00:00-05:00" n="1218" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1218">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 EW 1939/10–1844:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-18T21:00:00+03:00">October 18, 1944—9 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received October 18—6 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3981. Moscow press for October 15 features announcement of complete
                                liberation of Ukraine, leading articles and about half total space
                                being devoted to this achievement and progress of reconstruction
                                there. <hi rend="italic">Pravda</hi> leader refers to Kiev, Kharkov,
                                and Lwow as being in a single and indissoluble family of Soviet
                                Ukrainian cities, thereby confirming previous indications that the
                                Soviet Government has abandoned any thought of returning Lwow to
                                Poland.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>